{"word":"διαβοάω","slug":"διαβοάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>διαβοάω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσομαι</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>-βοάσω</el> is aor1 <a href='S:subjunctive mood'>subj.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to shout out, proclaim, publish</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be the common talk</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to cry out</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to contend in shouting</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}